
[1]bellows

   BEL'LOWS, n. sing.and plu.[L.bulga] An instrument, utensil or machine
   for blowing fire, either in private dwellings or in forges, furnaces
   and shops. It is so formed as by being dilated and contracted, to
   inhale air by a lateral orifice which is opened and closed with a
   valve, and to propel it through a tube upon the fire.
